leave%20the%20INDIA%20bloc.%20%E2%80%9CMany%20people%20board%20a%20train%20from%20the%20originating%20station%2C%20but%20one%20cannot%20say%20who%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20fight%20against%20the%20BJP.%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20wants%20to%20leave%20the%20train%20now%2C%20and%20we%20welcome%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fimportant-pillar-of-the-india-bloc-congress-after-tmc-reiterates-solo-act-for-bengal%5C%22%3EBanerjee%20announced%20her%20decision%20to%20go%20it%20solo%20in%20the%20state%20for%20the%20upcoming%20general%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20the%20Congress%20central%20leadership%20has%20shown%20optimism%20about%20clinching%20a%20seat-sharing%20arrangement%20with%20TMC%2C%20the%20state%20leadership%2C%20including%20Pradesh%20Congress%20Committee%20chief%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Choudhury%20has%20remained%20critical%20of%20Banerjee.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02132510%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-01-at-6.05.55-PM.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221023%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02132510%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-01-at-6.05.55-PM.jpeg%201023w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02132510%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-01-at-6.05.55-PM-300x188.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695359%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22641%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELeft%20leaders%20with%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20Adhir%20Chowdhury.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Yatra%20has%20faced%20obstacles%20in%20West%20Bengal%20including%20vandalism%20of%20multiple%20posters%20and%20decorations%20welcoming%20Gandhi%20in%20the%20state%20and%20alleged%20%E2%80%98non-cooperation%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20state%20administration.%20The%20government%20also%20rejected%20the%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20appeal%20to%20let%20Gandhi%20have%20lunch%20at%20a%20government%20guest%20house%20in%20Malda%2C%20citing%20CM%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20the%20town.%20Banerjee%20also%20held%20a%20%E2%80%9CJonosangjog%20Yatra%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20a%20people-connect%20rally%20%E2%80%93%20along%20the%20route%20covered%20by%20Gandhi%20a%20day%20before.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETensions%20also%20flared%20around%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20convoy%20on%20February%201%20when%20a%20car%E2%80%99s%20windshield%20shattered.%20Chowdhury%20quickly%20alleged%20stone-pelting%20in%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20territory%2C%20implicating%20the%20TMC.%20This%20also%20resonated%20with%20other%20opposition%20parties%20like%20the%20CPI(M)%20and%20BJP.%20However%2C%20the%20central%20Congress%20leadership%20offered%20a%20different%20explanation%20and%20appeared%20to%20view%20this%20less%20as%20a%20TMC%20attack%20than%20the%20Bengal%20division.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMalda%20and%20Murshidabad%20%E2%80%93%20two%20districts%20with%20a%20high%20Muslim%20population%20had%20once%20been%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20traditional%20bastion.%20As%20leader%20of%20the%20party%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Adhir%20Chowdhury%20is%20a%20sitting%20MP%20of%20Baharampur%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat.%20The%20other%20Congress%20MP%20from%20the%20state%2C%20Abu%20Hasem%20Khan%20Choudhury%2C%20has%20been%20winning%20the%20Malda%20Dakshin%20seat%20since%202009.%20TMC%20sources%20claim%20that%20these%20were%20the%20two%20seats%20offered%20by%20Banerjee%20during%20the%20discussion%20on%20seat-sharing%20which%20the%20state%20Congress%20rejected.%20While%20Congress%20drew%20a%20blank%20from%20these%20districts%20in%20the%202021%20assembly%20election%20%E