0on%20to%20enrich%20their%20chosen%20fields.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20in%20the%20late%20%E2%80%9960s%20and%20early%2070s%20that%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20historians%2C%20including%20Chamapakalakshmi%2C%20Noboru%20Karashima%20and%20Y.%20Subbarayalu%2C%20emerged.%20With%20their%20serious%20interrogation%20of%20sources%20and%20their%20rigorous%20interpretation%2C%20they%20were%20engaged%20in%20substantively%20extending%20the%20horizon%20of%20historical%20enquiry.%20That%20was%20when%20the%20visionary%20founders%20of%20the%20history%20centre%20at%20JNU%20invited%20Champakalakshmi%20to%20join%20the%20faculty%20so%20as%20to%20give%20the%20Centre%20for%20Historical%20Studies%20a%20pan-Indian%20dimension%20in%20its%20research%20and%20teaching.%20Their%20decision%20reflected%20their%20vision%20of%20institution%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChampakalakshmi%E2%80%99s%20presence%20in%20JNU%2C%20from%201972%20until%20her%20retirement%20in%201997%2C%20was%20to%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20a%20mature%20incorporation%20of%20peninsular%20Indian%20history%20into%20the%20generally%20north%20Indian%20centric%20discourse%20of%20Indian%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20was%20first%20introduced%20to%20the%20scholarship%20of%20Professor%20R.%20Champakalakshmi%20as%20an%20MA%20student%20in%20Central%20University%2C%20Hyderabad%2C%20and%20that%20made%20me%20decide%20on%20the%20research%20area%20to%20pursue.%20The%20article%20recommended%20to%20us%20was%20her%20presidential%20address%20to%20the%20Ancient%20India%20section%20of%20the%20Indian%20History%20Congress%20in%201986%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98Urbanisation%20in%20South%20India%3A%20the%20Role%20of%20Ideology%20and%20Polity%E2%80%99.%20Deftly%20weaving%20evidence%20from%20the%20early%20centuries%20of%20the%20Common%20Era%20to%20those%20of%20the%20second%20millennium%20CE%20from%20the%20Tamil%20south%2C%20she%20emphasised%20the%20growth%20of%20urbanisation%20as%20part%20of%20social%20transformations%20engendered%20by%20multiple%20factors%2C%20foremost%20among%20them%20being%20political%20and%20ideological%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fan-era-called-champakalakshmi%5C%22%3EAn%20Era%20Called%20Champakalakshmi%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20article%20%E2%80%93%20the%20prestigious%20Mamidipudi%20Venkatarangaiah%20Memorial%20lecture%20she%20had%20delivered%20in%201989%20titled%20%E2%80%98Ideology%20and%20the%20State%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20revealed%20a%20precise%20analysis%20of%20religious%20institutions%2C%20where%20each%20statement%20revealed%20the%20depth%20of%20knowledge%20of%20the%20primary%20sources%2C%20be%20they%20inscriptions%20or%20texts%2C%20composed%20in%20Tamil%20or%20Sanskrit%2C%20and%20the%20firm%20positioning%20of%20religion%20and%20ideology%20within%20the%20socio-political%20contexts.%20Her%20work%20opened%20the%20eyes%20of%20generations%20of%20students%20like%20me%20on%20how%20to%20contextualise%20the%20study%20of%20socio-economic%20structures%20and%20ideological%20traditions.%20I%20consider%20myself%20fortunate%20that%20I%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20move%20to%20the%20Centre%20for%20Historical%20Studies%2C%20JNU%2C%20to%20work%20with%20this%20doyen%20of%20South%20Indian%20history%2C%20under%20whose%20joint%20supervision%20I%20completed%20my%20MPhil%20dissertation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChampakalakshmi%E2%80%99s%20first%20monograph%20was%20published%20in%201981%20and%20focused%20on%20Vaisnava%20iconography%20in%20the%20Tamil%20region.%20The%20richness%20of%20discussion%20of%20the%20various%20aspects%20of%20Vaisnavism%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%3Cem%3EPancaratra%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EVaikhanasa%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Eagama%3C%2Fem%3E%20tradition%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Evyuha%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Eavatara%3C%2Fem%3E%20concepts%2C%20the%20Tamil%20Sangam%20evidence%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Ealvar%3C%2Fem%3E%20bhakti%20traditions%20and%20the%20magnificent%20iconography%20of%20the%20early%20medieval%20period%20%E2%80%93%20make%20it%20a%20must%20even%20today%20for%20any%20researcher%20working%20on%20south%20Indian%20history%20and%2F%20or%20history%20of%20religious%20processes.%20Possibly%20due%20to%20her%20extensive%20fieldwork%20for%20this%20book%20and%20subsequent%20research%2C%20Champakalakshmi%E2%80%99s%20familiarity%20with%20every%20part%20of%20the%20Tamil%20region%20was%20obvious%20to%20her%20colleagues%20in%20the%20field%2C%20and%20it%20was%20very%20rare%20for%20anyone%20to%20dare%20challenge%20her%20on%20sources%20or%20historical%20issues%20related%20to%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20next%20major%20publication%20%3Cem%3ETrade%2C%20Ideology%20and%20Urbanisation%3A%20South%20India%20300%20BC%20to%20AD%201300%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1996)%20came%20out%20a%20decade-and-a-half%20later%2C%20comprising%20revised%20versions%20of%20several%20previously%20published%20articles.%20Bringing%20together%20years%20of%20painstaking%20research%20on%20the%20voluminous%20Tamil%20inscriptions%20spanning%20the%206th%20to%2013th%20century%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20complex%20literary%20evidence%20across%20more%20than%20a%20millennium%2C%20Champakalakshmi%20drew%20attention%20to%20the%20long%20history%20of%20urban%20centres%20patronised%20by%20the%20Pallavas%20and%20Cholas%20in%20particular%2C%20be%20it%20Kumbakonam%20in%20the%20Kaveri%20valley%2C%20Kanchipuram%20in%20the%20Palar%20valley%2C%20among%20others.%20That%20urbanisation%20cannot%20be%20understood%20simplistically%2C%20and%20that%20urban%20centres%20have%20many%20lives%2C%20or%20may%20lose%20their%20relevance%20over%20time%2C%20and%20the%20institutional%20fulcrum%20provided%20by%20agricultural%20development%2C%20state%20formation%20and%20expansion%2C%20and%20trading%20networks%20are%20crucial%20to%20these%20processes%20is%20brought%20out%20admirably%20in%20this%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20again%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20religious%20institutions%20like%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebrahmadeya%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20temple%20in%20promoting%20resource%20mobilisation%20and%20urban%20growth%20are%20revealed%20with%20aplomb%20by%20the%20scholar.%20Her%20brilliant%20analysis%20of%20the%20Brihadisvara%20temple%20as%20a%20royal%20project%2C%20from%20the%20choice%20of%20location%20so%20as%20to%20control%20the%20fluvial%20plains%20of%20the%20Kaveri%20delta%2C%20to%20its%20naming%20as%20Rajarajesvaram%2C%20its%20humongous%20size%20and%20iconographic%20plan%2C%20and%20its%20maintenance%20of%20retinues%20of%20service%20personnel%2C%20is%20unsurpassed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChampakalakshmi%20on%20occasion%20expressed%20her%20concerns%20regarding%20the%20larger%20politics%20of%20interpretation%20in%20the%20historical%20field.%20One%20instance%20where%20she%20pitched%20in%20fiercely%20was%20in%20her%20outright%20denunciation%20of%20the%20theory%20of%20Segmentary%20State%20propounded%20by%20the%20American%20historian%20Burton%20Stein%2C%20which%20posited%20that%20the%20early%20medieval%20Chola%20rulers%20did%20not%20have%20actual%20control%20over%20their%20vast%20dominions%2C%20and%20only%20possessed%20a%20ritual%20sovereignty%2C%20and%20that%20their%20patronage%20of%20the%20brahmanas%20and%20the%20Puranic%20sectarian%20traditions%20along%20with%20their%20building%20of%20numerous%20temples%20attested%20to%20this.%20This%20typical%20Indological%20position%20of%20seeing%20everything%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20brahmanical%20ritual%20and%20authority%2C%20which%20insidiously%20appears%20even%20today%2C%20melded%20with%20a%20new%20imperialist%20historiography%20and%20anthropology%20that%20reduced%20history%20to%20the%20enunciation%20of%20cultural%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoining%20other%20Indian%20scholars%20who%20roundly%20criticised%20such%20a%20view%2C%20Champakalakshmi%2C%20using%20her%20formidable%20understanding%20of%20sources%2C%20wrote%20a%20heavy%20critique%20of%20Stein%E2%80%99s%20thesis%20in%20a%20review%20in%20the%20well-known%20journal%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Economic%20and%20Social%20History%20Review%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1983).%20Yet%2C%20she%2C%20along%20with%20her%20colleagues%2C%20welcomed%20Stein%20to%20the%20CHS%20as%20a%20visiting%20professor%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20later.%20That%20was%20the%20spirit%20of%20academic%20debate%20and%20dialogue%20that%20Champakalakshmi%20and%20others%20fostered%20in%20the%20CHS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20retirement%2C%20Champakalakshmi%20published%20two%20other%20books%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%20Temple%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2001)%20and%20%3Cem%3EReligion%2C%20Tradition%20and%20Ideology%3A%20Pre-Colonial%20South%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2011)%2C%20both%20being%20authoritative%20and%20vast%20in%20scope.%20In%20a%20way%2C%20with%20these%20publications%20and%20the%20numerous%20lectures%20she%20gave%20after%20her%20move%20to%20Chennai%2C%20both%20within%20and%20outside%20India%2C%20religion%20once%20again%20became%20the%20focus%20of%20her%20historical%20eye%2C%20for%20her%20forays%20into%20research%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Madras%20in%20the%201950s%20and%2060s%20were%20related%20to%20Jainism.%20In%20the%20Introduction%20to%20the%20latter%20work%2C%20Champakalakshmi%20unequivocally%20rejects%20the%20notion%20of%20tradition%20as%20something%20that%20is%20monolithic%20or%20immutable%2C%20and%20eschews%20the%20terminology%20she%20used%20in%20the%20former%20book%20%E2%80%93%20Hindu%20%E2%80%93%20in%20favour%20of%20%E2%80%98brahmanical%E2%80%99%20while%20referring%20to%20the%20many%20forms%20of%20religious%20cults%20and%20practices%20mediated%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebrahmanas%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20%3Cem%3EReligion%2C%20Tradition%20and%20Ideology%3A%20Pre-Colonial%20South%20India%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3EChampakalakshmi%20covers%20the%20brahmanical%20and%20sramanic%20traditions%2C%20and%20a%20range%20of%20textual%2C%20epigraphic%2C%20archaeological%20and%20visual%20sources%20that%20reveal%20her%20immense%20scholarly%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20my%20early%20days%20in%20JNU%2C%20something%20that%20I%20was%20often%20asked%20in%20conversations%20was%20whether%20I%20was%20Champakalakshmi%E2%80%99s%20daughter%20or%20niece.%20I%20remember%20mentioning%20this%20to%20her.%20The%20twinkle%20in%20her%20eyes%20and%20her%20smile%20remain%20etched%20in%20my%20memory.%20As%20recently%20as%20six%20months%20ago%2C%20I%20had%20a%20WhatsApp%20message%20from%20someone%20in%20Trichy%20asking%20me%20for%20my%20mother%E2%80%99s%20book!%20Gurus%20are%20up%20there%20with%20one%E2%80%99s%20parents%20they%20say%2C%20and%20Prof.%20Champakalakshmi%E2%80%99s%20support%20in%20my%20early%20years%20in%20JNU%2C%20including%20talking%20to%20my%20parents%20when%20they%20got%20anxious%20about%20me%2C%20certainly%20meant%20that%20she%20occupied%20that%20place%20in%20my%20life.%20It%20has%20been%20many%20years%20since%20I%20was%20in%20touch%20with%20Prof.%20Champakalakshmi%3B%20but%20the%20life%20of%20the%20mind%20is%20such%20that%20even%20without%20physical%20contact%2C%20one%20may%20feel%20the%20line%20of%20communication%20through%20the%20generous%20academic%20output%20of%20one%20such%20as%20her.%20With%20students%20trained%20by%20her%20now%20teaching%20far%20and%20wide%20across%20the%20world%2C%20south%20Indian%20history%20is%20no%20longer%20on%20the%20margins.%20Although%20she%20will%20be%20missed%2C%20she%20has%20left%20behind%20an%20abiding%20legacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ER.%20Mahalakshmi%20teaches%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Historical%20Studies%2C%20JNU.%20She%20specialises%20on%20the%20pre-modern%20history%20of%20south%20India%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20religious%20traditions.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706859015000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02125550%2FIMG-20240130-WA0038.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fr-champakalakshmis-abiding-legacy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22We%20have%20lost%20a%20historian%20who%20helped%20to%20not%20only%20define%20historical%20scholarship%20in%20India%20but%20also%20p